<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ870824-0114 </DOCNO><HL> Italy's Balance of Payments</HL><DD> 08/24/87</DD><SO> WALL STREET JOURNAL (J)</SO><IN> EUROPMONETARY NEWS, FOREIGN EXCHANGE, TRADE (MON) </IN><DATELINE> ROME  </DATELINE><TEXT>   Italy's balance of payments swung to a deficit of 553 billion lire ($416 million) in July from a surplus of 1.46 trillion lire a year earlier, the Bank of Italy said. The July deficit was smaller than the 1.69 trillion lire deficit in June, the central bank said.    The figures for the balance of payments, which represents all flows of goods and funds into and out of a country, are provisional, and aren't seasonally adjusted. </TEXT></DOC>